newsitem.title: UK: NWE jet fuel pressured with avails plentiful.
newsitem.headline: NWE jet fuel pressured with avails plentiful.

text.p: European jet fuel remained under pressure on Friday in both the north and the Mediterranean.
The NWE market was quiet with poor margins making sellers reluctant to show barrels at the notionally assessed levels of around June IPE gas oil +$17.00 for cif cargoes.
June IPE gas oil closed $1.25 a tonne lower at $177.75.
Barges were pegged at a steady June IPE +$16.50 a tonne fob ARA.
In the Med, non-EU spec Libyan material was plentiful, and values slipped to high fob quotes +$3.00 fob Zawai and +$5.00-$6.00 fob Ras Lanuf.
EU spec material was pegged at high fob quotes +$6.00-$7.00 a tonne.
